Tab state persists across hover sessions instead of resetting to 'API Limits' default tab.

**Bug:** When user switches to 'Subscription Usage' tab, then moves mouse away (collapsing panel), the tab state persists. On re-hover, 'Subscription Usage' remains active.

**Expected:** Tab should reset to 'API Limits' when panel closes/reopens.

**Root Cause:** activeTab state variable not reset when showDetails becomes false (ClaudeUsageBar.svelte:23).

**Proposed Fix:**
```svelte
$effect(() => {
    if (\!showDetails) {
        activeTab = 'api-limits';
    }
});
```

**Found In:** jat-bk0 QA testing
**Report:** dashboard/docs/qa-report-claude-usage-bar.md

